    created createdTime [note: 'business desc: Timestamp automatically captured when the record is first created, supporting audit trails and chronological tracking., technical desc: Type: createdTime, field ID: fldLj07Z9sCcOm1DC, readonly field: true']
    last_modified_by lastModifiedBy [note: 'business desc: Automatically records the user who made the most recent update to the project brief. Useful for tracking collaboration and accountability., technical desc: Type: lastModifiedBy, field ID: fld79bNf1ktlI4Gl4, readonly field: true']
    campaign_creative_assets checkbox [note: 'business desc: Indicates whether the client will provide creative assets for the campaign. If not selected, the internal design team will generate artwork based on campaign requirements., technical desc: Type: checkbox, field ID: fldrUQmVvz1YAJFxs, readonly field: false']
    actual_q formula [note: 'business desc: This formula compares the quarter of created to the current quarter (based on TODAY()) within the same year. It returns: Q0 if the date is in the same quarter as the current one. Q-1, Q-2, or Q-3 if it is 1, 2, or 3 quarters earlier, respectively. An empty value if it falls outside that range or in a different year. Use this to determine which quarter (relative to the current quarter) a record belongs to—helpful for segmenting or tracking past events within the current year., technical desc: Type: formula, field ID: fldjeCEwYVYEcYcis, readonly field: true']
    quarter_of_the_year formula [note: 'business desc: This formula determines the quarter (Q1, Q2, Q3, or Q4) for the date in start_date and appends the respective year. The first part uses the month to calculate which quarter the date falls into; the second part adds the four-digit year. As a result, regardless of whether the date is in a past, current, or future year, you’ll see the quarter followed by the year, such as “Q3 2022” or “Q1 2025.” This is useful for quickly identifying the specific quarter and year of any given date., technical desc: Type: formula, field ID: fld3v4OSrABVs3uLF, readonly field: true']
    project_brief_rel multipleRecordLinks [note: 'business desc: Connects projects to their brief documents. Provides context., technical desc: Type: multipleRecordLinks, Reference to project_brief table, field ID: fldkCCTDpCpN1VOua, readonly field: false']
    record_id_from_project_brief_rel multipleLookupValues [note: 'business desc: ID linking records to project briefs. Stores numerical IDs., technical desc: Type: multipleLookupValues, field ID: fldS6bdfqfWIGWF5O, readonly field: false']
